dct_title_s: Reconnoissance of the western coast of the United States from Monterey to the Columbia River in three sheets, sheet no. 2
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Depths shown by soundings. Includes views: Trinidad Head -- Cape Mendocino. "Verified by I.I. Stevens, Lieut. U.S. Engrs. & Bvt. Major, asst. in charge of office." Includes sailing directions from Cape Mendocino to the Umpqua River. Shows tracks of U.S. Coast Survey Schooner Ewing.
dct_publisher_sm: [Washington, D.C.] : U.S. Coast Survey Office, Published in 1850.
